64256,lobbying.ie/return/64256/limerick-chamber,Limerick Chamber,21/01/2021 23:01,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Urgent meeting on crisis at Shannon airport,"Hildegarde Naughton|Super Junior Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Kieran O'Donnell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe Carey|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Willie O'Dea|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Maurice Quinlivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Patrick O'Donovan|Minister of State|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Niall Collins|Minister of State|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science::Richard O'Donoghue|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul Gavan|Senator|Seanad::Alan Kelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Martin Browne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Lowry|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mattie McGrath|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Timmy Dooley|Senator|Seanad::Seán Kelly|MEP|European Parliament::Róisín Garvey|Senator|Seanad::Pauline O'Reilly|Senator|Seanad","1) highlight critical importance of regional connectivity through Shannon airport to the over 1,300 members organisations, who support more than 105,000 jobs across the Mid West and West as represented by Limerick Chamber, Ennis Chamber, Shannon Chamber and Galway Chamber.::2) urge the Minister to develop support packages for main carriers into the country Aer Lingus and Ryanair, as has been done in other EU states, and to attach conditions around carbon emission reduction targets and regional route restoration together with further regional route development::3) request for Shannon group to be allowed to cross-subsidise route development with airlines and cargo operations development within the airport  using funds generated in other areas of the group::4) seek the earliest appoint of a Chair to Shannon Group::5) seek that national aviation policy be aligned with stated goals of Project Ireland 2040,  namely the promotion of balanced regional development, recognising that direct business routes into strategic destinations is critical for growing industry clusters in regional cities.","Letter to Ministers Ryan and Naughton outlining proposed urgent measures in support of Shannon Airport was issued on 8th September.|Letter|1::Meeting held with Minister Ryan and Minster Naughton on Monday 14th September. Followed by release of joint statement on behalf of Chambers to local media in Limerick, Clare and Galway  www.limerickchamber.ie/joint-chambers-meet-with-ministers-ryan-and-naughton-on-shannon-airport/|Virtual Meeting|1::Email advising constiuency TD's of communications with Minister Ryan and Naughton, including a copy of letter to Ministers outlining proposed measures in support of Shannon airport, was circulated to TD's in Limerick, Clare and Galway.|Email|1","Dee Ryan and Dr Catriona Cahill accompanied by president of Limerick Chamber and the CEOs & Presidents of Galway, Shannon and Ennis Chambers",No,,False,,False,
