64364,lobbying.ie/return/64364/ibec,Ibec,21/01/2021 15:34,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Economic Development and Industry,Ibec's 'Reboot & Reimagine' and 'Ibec Budget 2021' Campaigns,James Browne|Minister of State|Department of Justice and Equality::Oonagh McPhillips|Deputy Secretary|Department of Justice and Equality,"Ensure awareness of Ibec's 'Reboot & Reimagine' campaign, which aims to galvanise all stakeholders on a set of actions and aspirations to create a sustainable future for Ireland in the wake of COVID-19::Support for Ibec's 'Budget 2021' campaign priorities, particularly: Preparing for a no-deal Brexit; getting people back to work and business investing; ensuring our inward and outward FDI model remains competitive; and investing in quality of life and the low carbon transition",|Email|2-5::|Letter|2-5,"Danny McCoy, Ibec CEO",No,,False,,False,
64365,lobbying.ie/return/64365/ibec,Ibec,21/01/2021 15:33,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Economic Development and Industry,"Agriculture, food, and the marine priorities - Ibec's 'Reboot & Reimagine' and 'Ibec Budget 2021' Campaigns","Brendan Gleeson|Secretary General|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Charlie McConalogue|Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine","Avoidance of a detrimental no-deal Brexit trading scenario for the agri-food and drink sector, the injection of additional liquidity into the Irish food supply chain, the expansion of export opportunities for the sector and the delivery of a whole sector approach to climate action::Revitalisation of the national afforestation programme::Support for the growth and potential of our maritime economy::Ensure awareness of Ibec's Budget 2021 priorities: Preparing for a no-deal Brexit , getting people back to work and business investing , our inward and outward FDI model remaining competitive and investment in quality of life and the low carbon transition",|Email|2-5::|Letter|2-5,"Danny McCoy, Ibec CEO",No,,False,,False,
