64742,lobbying.ie/return/64742/lauralynn-irelands-childrens-hospice,LauraLynn Ireland's Children's Hospice,21/01/2021 21:28,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Budgetary matters,Budget 2021 - LauraLynn Children's Hospice 2021 Pre-Budget Submission.,"Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Josepha Madigan|Minister of State|Department of Education and Skills::Richard Boyd Barrett|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neale Richmond|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Simon Harris|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Catherine Martin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ossian Smyth|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To inform Government of LauraLynn's 2021 Pre-Budget Submission requests and seek to influence budget decisions and achieve core funding for its children's hospice service.,"Soft copy letter with  LauraLynn's  2021 Pre-Budget Submission outlining LauraLynn's demands and requirements for dedicated hospice funding in Budget 2021 attached.

Letters were distributed by email to: Ministers for Health, Finance, Children and Public Expenditure & Reform and also to the Chair of  the Health Committee between 18.9.2020 - 22.9.2020|Letter|2-5::Targeted e-mail was sent  with LauraLynn's 2021 Pre-Budget Submission attached outlining LauraLynn's demands and requirements for dedicated hospice funding in Budget 2021.

Emails sent between 22.9.2020 - 25.9.2020 -to local TDs in Dublin Rathdown and Dun Laoghaire constituencies.  Also sent to the Simon Harris. T.D.'s constituency|Email|6-10::Virtual meeting on 15.10.2020 with Minister for Health Stephen Donnelly T.D. to discuss LauraLynn's Pre-Budget Submission and funding requirements.|Virtual Meeting|1",Sarah O'Callaghan,No,,True,LauraLynn Staff were asked to bring the LauraLynn 2021 Pre Budget Submission (including the key demands) to the attention of their constituency TD's (by email) requesting their support.,False,
