65524,lobbying.ie/return/65524/friends-of-the-earth,Friends of the Earth,20/01/2021 21:33,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Environment,Climate Action and Low Carbon Development (Amendment) Bill 2020,"Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alice-Mary Higgins|Senator|Seanad::Lynn Boylan|Senator|Seanad::Timmy Dooley|Senator|Seanad::John McGahon|Senator|Seanad::Pauline O'Reilly|Senator|Seanad::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Whitmore|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Christopher O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Réada Cronin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Éamon Ó Cuív|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Leo Varadkar|An Tánaiste|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Paul Kenny|Special Adviser|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport",Close the loopholes in the bill to ensure faster and fairer climate action,"Friends of the Earth, Oisin Coghlan sent emails to members of the Oireachtas Committee on climate action, specifically to communicate suggestions on amendments to the climate action and low carbon development act, specifically in line with the recommendations in this briefing prepared by Stop Climate Chaos
https://www.stopclimatechaos.ie/assets/files/pdf/what_needs_to_change_in_the_climate_bill_-_scc_briefing_oct_2020.pdf
Jerry MacEvilly sent emails to Timmy Dooley ( 3rd Nov, 17 Nov, 18 19 20 Nov). Cormac Devlin( 3rd Nov, 17, 18 Nov). Christopher O'Sullivan emailed on 17 Nov and 4, 7 and 8 Dec, and emails to Paul Kenny Special Advisor.|Email|21-30::Friends of the Earth participated in a virtual meeting with TD's on December 7th 2020, where we asked all TD's to attend for a specfic meeting with their constituents on the climate action and low carbon development act. In advance we shared with our members specific points to amend the Climate Action and Low Carbon Development Act, in line with this briefing https://www.stopclimatechaos.ie/assets/files/pdf/what_needs_to_change_in_the_climate_bill_-_scc_briefing_oct_2020.pdf

Approximately 90 virtual meetings occured on that day, many of which included people who were attending because Friends of the Earth asked them to attend.  It is not possible for us to know which meetings were attended by people because Friends of the Earth asked them, as many other groups also asked their supporters to attend.  TD's who were met by specific Friends of the Earth staff included|Virtual Meeting|51-100::Phone calls by Oisin Coghlan, Jerry MacEvilly with members of the Oireachtas Committee on Climate Action and their staff during the course of debates on the Climate Action and Low Carbon Development Act in  November and December 2020.
Phone calls by Oisin Coghlan to Paul Kenny, Special Advisor during the course of the debates on the Climate Action and Low Carbon Development Act.|Phone call|6-10","Oisin Coghlan, Kate Ruddock, Jerry MacEvilly, Aine O'Gorman",No,,True,"Close the loopholes in the climate bill to ensure faster and fairer climate action, specifically as per the briefing prepared by Stop Climate Choas, available at this link https://www.stopclimatechaos.ie/assets/files/pdf/briefing_for_participants_in_the_td_lobby_for_faster_and_fairer_climate_action_december_2020.pdf",False,
