65560,lobbying.ie/return/65560/oxfam-ireland,Oxfam Ireland,21/01/2021 17:09,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,"Foreign Affairs ",As part of the Irish Coalition on Business and Human Rights advocated for Ireland's support for the development of a UN binding treaty on business and human rights.,Simon Coveney|Minister|Department of Foreign Affairs,That the Irish Government support the development of a UN treaty on business and human rights.  That it follow other EU member states and directly address the OEIGWG 6th Session on priority issues; that it develop and share a clear position on the UN Treaty; that it take action within the EU to ensure a clear negotiation mandate for the next OEIGWG session in 2021.,|Letter|1,"Jim Clarken, CEO",No,,False,,False,
