65791,lobbying.ie/return/65791/children-in-hospital-ireland,Children in Hospital Ireland,20/01/2021 16:20,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Health,"Providing information on the findings and recommendations of Children in Hospital Ireland’s research report ‘Childhood Illness, Financial Stress - The Hidden Costs of Hospital Care for Children’. The report focused on the non-medical costs associated with having a child in hospital and the financial supports available to families.","Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Erin McGreehan|Senator|Seanad::Joe Carey|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joan Collins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul Donnelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Charles Flanagan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Claire Kerrane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Marc Ó Cathasaigh|Councillor|Waterford City and County Council::Éamon Ó Cuív|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paddy Burke|Senator|Seanad::Róisín Garvey|Senator|Seanad::Paul Gavan|Senator|Seanad::Eugene Murphy|Senator|Seanad::Mark Wall|Senator|Seanad::Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Heather Humphreys|Minister|Department of Social Protection::Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Joe O'Brien|Minister of State|Department of Rural and Community Development::Frank Feighan|Minister of State|Department of Health::Anne Rabbitte|Minister of State|Department of Health::Pauline O'Reilly|Senator|Seanad::Kathleen Funchion|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Patrick Costello|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cathal Crowe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Dillon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe Flaherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Paul Phelan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Sherlock|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mark Ward|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Whitmore|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mary Fitzpatrick|Senator|Seanad::Sharon Keogan|Senator|Seanad::Lynn Ruane|Senator|Seanad::Mary Seery Kearney|Senator|Seanad::Michael Moynihan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Holly Cairns|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Canney|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Emer Higgins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Murnane O'Connor|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pauline Tully|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Violet Anne Wynne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ivana Bacik|Senator|Seanad::Alice-Mary Higgins|Senator|Seanad::Fiona O'Loughlin|Senator|Seanad::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Crowe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Gino Kenny|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Lahart|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Frances Black|Senator|Seanad::Lorraine Clifford-Lee|Senator|Seanad::Martin Conway|Senator|Seanad::Annie Hoey|Senator|Seanad::Seán Kyne|Senator|Seanad::Denis Naughten|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jackie Cahill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",Greater awareness of the financial issues that families with children in hospital face because of the non-financial expenses associated with a child's hospitalisation.,"An email was sent containing a copy of the report and a letter highlighting some of the report's main findings and recommendations. This was sent (individually) to relevant Ministers, Ministers of State, Party Spokespeople, and members of relevant Oireachtas Committees.|Email|1::Anna Gunning (CEO) invited Jennifer Carroll MacNeill TD, by email, to set up a virtual meeting to discuss the findings and recommendations of the Children in Hospital report.|Email|1::Anna Gunning (CEO) and Laura Austen-Gray (Advocacy Officer) presented the report's findings and recommendations to Jennifer Carroll MacNeill TD. Potential ways to highlight the issue (such as an opinion piece in the newspapers) and gain additional information on the topic (Parliamentary Questions) were discussed.|Virtual Meeting|1::Two follow up emails were sent to thank Deputy MacNeill for attending the meeting and to provide additional information (e.g. a copy of the report, summary of main findings, examples of existing models).|Email|2-5::Laura Austen-Gray (Advocacy Officer) and Senator Erin McGreehan exchanged emails regarding setting up a virtual meeting, to discuss the findings and recommendations of Children in Hospital Ireland's report.|Email|2-5::A submission was sent to the Joint Committee on Disability Matters. This was in response to Committee's invitation for 'written submissions from interested groups or individuals to hear about the lived experience of people with disabilities on the issues that affect them and their families and/or carers'. Children in Hospital Ireland’s submission outlined a number of issues facing the families of children with disabilities who experienced repeated and/or prolonged hospital stays. Most of the issues raised within the submission arose from the research report ‘Childhood Illness, Financial Stress - The Hidden Costs of Hospital Care for Children’.|Submission|1",Anna Gunning (CEO),No,,False,,False,
