65980,lobbying.ie/return/65980/dublin-chamber-of-commerce,Dublin Chamber of Commerce,21/01/2021 16:17,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Budgetary matters,Communication to Budgetary Oversight Committee regarding Budget 2021,"Richard Boyd Barrett|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Canney|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ciaran Cannon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mairéad Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Healy-Rae|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Lahart|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Aindrias Moynihan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ged Nash|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Willie O'Dea|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Kieran O'Donnell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Patricia Ryan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To request an opportunity to present to the Budgetary Oversight Committee on Dublin Chamber’s key priorities for Budget 2021.::Reform and consider extension of the Employment Wage Subsidy Scheme.::To support employees and improve the Labour Market.::To boost investment in Irish Enterprise and introduce a 20% Capital Gain Tax rate for investment in SMEs.::To accelerate the transition to a Green Economy and prioritise sustainable infrastructure investment in the GDA.,Emails exchanged with the named DPOs|Email|1::Dublin Chamber's 2021 pre-budget Submission was shared with the named DPOs|Submission|1,Fergus Sharpe,No,,False,,False,
65981,lobbying.ie/return/65981/dublin-chamber-of-commerce,Dublin Chamber of Commerce,21/01/2021 16:16,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Communication to Taoiseach Micheal Martin regarding Govt. Covid-19 strategy & impact on tourism and hospitality sector,"Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Martin Fraser|Secretary General|Department of the Taoiseach::John Shaw|Assistant Secretary|Department of the Taoiseach","To communicate the growing concerns in the business community regarding the medium-to-long-term strategy for coping with the Covid-19 pandemic and its likely economic impact.::To highlight the need for a specific government plan to support the tourism, hospitality and events industries.::To highlight the need from a business perspective for a comprehensive testing, tracking, and isolation system to be put in place to ensure accurate & sufficient data.",Email exchanged with the named DPOs|Email|1::Letter exchanged with the named DPOs|Letter|1,Aebhric McGibney,No,,False,,False,
