66037,lobbying.ie/return/66037/aercap-holdings-nv,AerCap Holdings N.V.,20/01/2021 16:26,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Transport,"Following on from participation in the Irish government-established Aviation Recovery Task Force, correspondence and discussions in relation to the implication of Covid-19 on the aviation sector and the best practice responses being observed globally.","Fintan Towey|Assistant Secretary|Department of Transport, Tourism and Sport::Ken Spratt|Assistant Secretary|Department of Transport, Tourism and Sport::Hildegarde Naughton|Super Junior Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment","A balanced approach to Irish aviation policy that would ensure safe air travel protocols (including the use of best practice responses being observed globally and of emerging testing approaches) while recognising the importance of aviation to Ireland as an island, both in terms of access for citizens/travellers and the broader economic considerations (including but not limited to the impact on AerCap’s airline customers).",|Virtual Meeting|2-5::|Email|1::|Phone call|1,"Aengus Kelly, CEO",No,,False,,False,
