66062,lobbying.ie/return/66062/dublin-chamber-of-commerce,Dublin Chamber of Commerce,21/01/2021 16:08,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Communication with Minister Heather Humphreys on remote and flexible working,Heather Humphreys|Minister|Department of Social Protection,"To promote the recommendations contained in Dublin Chamber’s submission on remote working to the Department of Business, Enterprise and Innovation;::To target labour re-skilling activities to support the development of the green economy and to consider use of EU Green Deal::To consider remote working as complementary rather than disruptive to the urban agenda;::To encourage all-Ireland cooperation on regional development;::To maintain support for a city-regions based approach to regional development;",Meeting with the named DPO|Virtual Meeting|1,Fergus Sharpe,No,,False,,False,
