66106,lobbying.ie/return/66106/irish-cancer-society,Irish Cancer Society,21/01/2021 11:12,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Health,Pre-Budget 2021,"Paul Daly|Senator|Seanad::Micheál Carrigy|Senator|Seanad::Emer Currie|Senator|Seanad::Mark Daly|Senator|Seanad::Mary Fitzpatrick|Senator|Seanad::Annie Hoey|Senator|Seanad::Erin McGreehan|Senator|Seanad::Alan Kelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Catherine Connolly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ged Nash|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jackie Cahill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Sorca Clarke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Dillon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul Donnelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Peadar Tóibín|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mary Lou McDonald|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach","Ring-fenced funding for the National Cancer Strategy::Funding to address COVID-19 related backlogs in cancer services::Addressing reductions in capacity (due to social distancing) by making immediate investment in temporary builds while committing to overdue capital investment in oncology day wards, operating theatres, elective-only hospitals and a comprehensive cancer centre.::Expedited delivery of Sláintecare::Funding of Endoscopy Action Plan::Reduction in the Drugs Payment Scheme::Abolition of prescription charges::Reduction of car parking charges at public hospitals::Abolition of inpatient charges::Provision of life-long medical cards to those with a terminal cancer diagnosis and survivors of childhood or adolescent cancer::Provision of medical cards to all cancer patients upon diagnosis until treatment has finished::Extension of publicly funded fertility preservation services to children and adolescent cancer patients::Increase to state funding for Night Nursing services::Ring-fenced funding for cancer research::Funding for skin cancer prevention plan::20% of the national transport budget to walking and cycling projects::An increase in excise on cigarettes by 80c and excise alignment on roll-your-own tobacco in line with cigarettes.::Funding for proven smoking quit supports::To thank Deputy Alan Kelly for his contributions during Leader's Questions on 10.09.2020 and emphasise our desire that there is no change to BreastCheck screening intervals.","Email to Alan Kelly TD 10.09.2020; Email 18.09.2020 to Senators Paul Daly, Michael Carrigy, Emer Currie, Mark Daly, Mary Fitzpatrick, Annie Hoey, Erin McGreehan, and Deputies Alan Kelly, Catherine Connolly, Ged Nash, Jackie Cahill, Sorca Clarke, David Cullinane, Cormac Devlin, Alan Dillon, Paul Donnelly, Bernard Durkan, Alan Farrell, Neasa Hourigan, Roisín Shortall, Peadar Tóibín; Email to Minister Micheal McGrath September 30 2020; Email to An Taoiseach Micheal Martin 08.10.2020; Email to Deputy Bernard Durkan 08.10.2020|Email|21-30::Meeting with Deputies Mary Lou McDonald and David Cullinane 21.09.2020. Paul Gordon (Irish Cancer Society) in attendance.|Virtual Meeting|1::Zoom Briefing hosted by the Irish Cancer Society 18.09.2020. Senators Paul Daly, Michael Carrigy, Emer Currie, Mark Daly, Mary Fitzpatrick, Annie Hoey, Erin McGreehan, and Deputies Alan Kelly, Catherine Connolly, Ged Nash, Jackie Cahill, Sorca Clarke, David Cullinane, Cormac Devlin, Alan Dillon, Paul Donnelly, Bernard Durkan, Alan Farrell, Neasa Hourigan, Roisín Shortall, Peadar Tóibín in attendance.|Event / Reception|1","Rachel Morrogh, Director of Advocacy and External Relations",No,,False,,False,
