66388,lobbying.ie/return/66388/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:06,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,"Correspondence with Department of Health officials re workforce planning concerns in nursing home sector, exacerbated by Covid-19 pandemic.",Gerry O'Brien|Director|Department of Health,"To have issues relating to workforce planning in the nursing home sector adequately addressed as the sector faces the challenges presented by Covid-19 pandemic. There is a severe shortage of Healthcare Assistants in the nursing home and broader healthcare sector and requirement presents to remove the role from the Ineligible Categories of Employment Listing on a restricted basis. Furthermore, necessity to implement long-term workforce plan for health services to meet growth in requirement",Letter informing of significant workforce planning concerns in nursing home sector.|Letter|1::|Email|2-5,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
