66397,lobbying.ie/return/66397/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:05,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,"Follow-up letter to Minister for Health after meeting with Minister Donnelly, Minister Butler and Department of Health officials on 1st December",Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,"Ensuring a joint communication strategy led by Department of Health to include Nursing Homes Ireland, HPSC and HSE on the requirement for vigilance by visitors to nursing homes and other long-term residential care settings, and personal responsibility given the threat of Covid-19 as outlined by CMO and NPHET.::NHI recommends that a reviewed model of funding for nursing home care be prioritised to enable all nursing homes to offer equivalent terms & conditions to all staff grades that are currently offered by HSE for similar work to recognise the care provided by committed staff.::NHI requests to also add nominated visitors to residents to the priority list for Covid-19 vaccinations.","Follow-up letter on specific agenda items, our discussions and
agreed action points from meeting on 1st December.|Letter|1","Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
