66402,lobbying.ie/return/66402/ibm,IBM,21/01/2021 12:02,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,"To provide an update on recent developments in IBM globally and in Ireland. To update on progress with the P-TECH programme, and the potential for the SkillsBuild programme in relation to SME skills. To discuss digitalization in the public services.","Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Matthew Lynch|Special Adviser|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment","The Minister's support for extension of the P-TECH pilot beyond the initial three schools.::The Minister's guidance on whether the SkillsBuild programme might be most relevant to his Department or the Dept of Higher Education & Research.::To inform the Minister of IBM's local capabilities in technologies relevant to public service digitalisation, specifically Digital Health Pass.","Virtual meeting on Nov 24.
P-TECH in Ireland: https://ptech.org/p-tech-network/our-schools/irl/
SkillsBuild: https://www.ibm.org/initiatives/skillsbuild|Virtual Meeting|1",Paul Farrell,No,,False,,False,
66403,lobbying.ie/return/66403/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:13,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Letter to Minister for Health re amendments to Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS),Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health,"To highlight the ongoing need for TAPS to ensure nursing homes can meet the costs associated with implementing the recommendations of the Nursing Homes Expert Panel, and that TAPS needs to be examined in the wake of these recommendations::To state NHI's strong concerns regarding the scope of the Nursing Home Support Scheme (Fair Deal), in its current construct, to support nursing homes in achieving the recommendations.",|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
