66406,lobbying.ie/return/66406/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:03,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Follow-up letter to Minister for Health after meeting with Minister Donnelly on 5th November re Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS),Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health,To highlight that TAPS is not the vehicle in supporting the implementation of the Expert Panel recommendations and it is acknowledged that many of the recommendations have longer term implications which go beyond the timeframe and limitations of the current temporary scheme.,|Letter|1::|Virtual Meeting|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
