66417,lobbying.ie/return/66417/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:15,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Engagement with Department of Health official re guidance issued relating to visitations to long-term residential care facilities.,Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,Review of current guidance needed to take account of the festive season and to give nursing home care providers adequate time to prepare for facilitation of safe visits to nursing homes during the Christmas period in the context of Covid-19 pandemic.,|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66422,lobbying.ie/return/66422/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:21,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Letter to Department of Health official re Nursing Homes Expert Panel recommendations,Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,To provide Department of Health with results of survey undertaken by NHI of its' Members regarding the Expert Panel Recommendations with regard to implmentation of recommended measures to prevent and manage Covid19,|Letter|1::Email with results of survey mentioned attached.|Email|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66423,lobbying.ie/return/66423/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:21,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Letter to Department of Health official re serial testing in nursing homes,Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,Confirmation of decision by NPHET to continue serial testing programme in nursing homes. The serial testing programme is absolutely critical for early detection of Covid19 and to support nursing homes in timely implementation of measures required where Covid-positive tests present::To propose increased frequency in testing particularly in regions/locations with high instances of community transmission of Covid-19.,|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66424,lobbying.ie/return/66424/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:22,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Engagement with Minister for Health re extension of Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS) in the context of Nursing Homes Expert Panel recommendations,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health,"In respect of Nursing Homes Expert Panel recommendations, to put forward to the Minister the need of Government to commit additional resources to the nursing home sector to ensure the critical recommendations become reality::To highlight need for resourcing separate to TAPS as the recommendations of Expert Panel have long-term implications in implementing a structure that greater integrates nursing home care within our health services",|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66427,lobbying.ie/return/66427/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:03,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Engagement with Department of Health official re Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS),Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,To highlight the need for the Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme to recognise costs being incurred to manage and prevent Covid19 within nursing homes but not encompassed under the Scheme. For example: the setting aside and maintenance of rooms used for isolation purposes.,|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66428,lobbying.ie/return/66428/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:22,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,"Letter to Department of Health official re: public health guidance on visits to long-term residential care facilities, serial testing, communication between NHI and Department of Health, and Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS)",Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,To reiterate NHI proposal to agree on an early warning system to indicate a prevalence or danger of infection in geographical area be developed for nursing homes.::To outline the need for immediate engagement on the continued funding requirements via TAPS for the sector to ensure continuity of service provision.,|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66429,lobbying.ie/return/66429/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:03,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Letter to Minister for Health re the need for continuation of Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme post original schedule deadline of September 30th to ensure nursing homes continue to have substantive costs to manage and prevent Covid19 recognised in their day-to-day efforts to protect nursing home residents and staff from the virus,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health,Seeking engagement and immediate consultation with Department of Health re requirement to maintain additional funding post September 30th as clearly the significant challenges associated with Covid19 in respect of nursing homes remain.,|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
66431,lobbying.ie/return/66431/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:26,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Letter to Minister for Health re Covid-19 Nursing Homes Expert Panel Report: Implementation Oversight Team,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,"To note NHI's disappointment in its exclusion from the Implementation Oversight Team. Given that the overriding recommendation from the Panel is the integration of private nursing homes into the wider framework of public health and social care, it is inexplicable that NHI as the representative for the majority provider has been excluded.",|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
