66654,lobbying.ie/return/66654/the-irish-farmers-association---ifa,The Irish Farmers' Association - IFA,20/01/2021 22:32,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Agriculture,Preparing for the End of the Transition Period - Brexit Readiness Action Plan (September 2020),"Charlie McConalogue|Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Martin Heydon|Minister of State|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Pippa Hackett|Super Junior Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Paul Savage|Assistant Secretary|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Cecil Beamish|Assistant Secretary|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach::John Callinan|Second Secretary General|Department of the Taoiseach",Full engagement with the Department of Agriculture and the Government on the country's readiness as we come towards the end of the Transition Period::That delays in movements of goods would be avoided::That departure from the Northern Ireland protocol would be unacceptable,|Virtual Meeting|2-5::|Email|2-5::|Informal communication|2-5,"Tim Cullinan IFA President, Bryan Barry IFA Deputy Director General, Elaine Farrell IFA Oireachtas Executive",No,,False,,False,
66655,lobbying.ie/return/66655/the-irish-farmers-association---ifa,The Irish Farmers' Association - IFA,20/01/2021 22:05,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Resilience and Recovery 2020-2021: Plan for Living with COVID-19,Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Deirdre Gillane|Chief of Staff|Department of the Taoiseach::Diarmuid Lynch|Special Adviser|Department of the Taoiseach,"To ensure that all parts of the Food Chain remain operational and the marts are able to function::To highlight that since the start of the COVID-19 Pandemic, the farming community has played its part in producing vital raw materials for food production",|Informal communication|2-5::|Letter|1,Tim Cullinan IFA President,No,,False,,False,
66656,lobbying.ie/return/66656/the-irish-farmers-association---ifa,The Irish Farmers' Association - IFA,21/01/2021 17:28,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Agriculture,Ash Dieback,"Jackie Cahill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Carthy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Collins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Fitzmaurice|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe Flaherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul Kehoe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Ring|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad::Lynn Boylan|Senator|Seanad::Paul Daly|Senator|Seanad::Tim Lombard|Senator|Seanad::Denis O'Donovan|Senator|Seanad","To highlight that the newly introduced Reconstitution and Underplanting Scheme (Ash Dieback) does not adequately support forest owners for the financial losses incurred and must be redesigned to support owners to reconstitute all infected plantations and remove the replanting obligation under certain circumstances.::To ensure that farmers affected by the disease are appropriately supported to manage infected plantations, all infected plantations (both grant aided and non-grant aided) must be eligible for a 100% reconstitution grant to support forest owners to clearfell and replant with tree species that satisfy their management objectives.::That forest premiums be paid on replanted land for 15 years according to GPC (Grant and Premium Categories) rates established::That the option not to replant, without penalties, must also be available under certain circumstances",|Email|2-5::|Informal communication|2-5::|Virtual Meeting|1,"Tim Cullinan IFA President, Vincent Nally IFA Farm Forestry Chair, Geraldine O'Sullivan IFA Farm Forestry Executive",No,,False,,False,
