66815,lobbying.ie/return/66815/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:16,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Trade,"Raised concerns about lack of customs preparation in advance of 1st Jan 2021, raised concerns about difficulties members are experiencing using AIS, highlighted the need for alternatives to the landbridge as delays at British ports is likely, asked for details on potential continuation of Bord Bia Quality Assurance scheme in Northern Ireland and raised concerns about the impact of reduced air freight capacity on exporters.",Simon Coveney|Minister|Department of Foreign Affairs::Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach,"Government to assess customs preparedness, look into the use of AIS, ensure that Irish trucks are not stuck at British ports and consider the impact of reduced air freight capacity on trade, in particular exporters.",Took place at a meeting of the DFA's Brexit Stakeholders Forum|Virtual Meeting|1,Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
66828,lobbying.ie/return/66828/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:11,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Finance,"2021 Budget: Establish an export credit agency, highlight the need for signalling intention with employment supports, particularly the EWSS, set up an independent and wide-reaching State-owned credit lending institution, support Brexit related training and supports, support alternatives to the landbridge, swift transition to a zero-emissions economy, accompany increased carbon tax with a reduction in reduction in the VAT-rate for renewable technologies and increased rail network for freight.",Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform,For the Department of Finance and the Department of Public Expenditure and Reform to take the Irish Exporters Associations' proposals into consideration when drafting Budget 2021.,IEA 2021 pre-budget submission is available on our website: https://irishexporters.ie/submissions/iea-submission-2021-pre-budget-submission/|Submission|1,Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
66829,lobbying.ie/return/66829/coillte-cga,Coillte CGA,21/01/2021 17:22,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Agriculture,"Joint letter from Coillte, Forsa and SIPTU to the Ministers of Agriculture and Forestry seeking additional resourcing for the Forestry Appeals Commission (FAC) so that appeals against felling licences could be held in a timely manner and that the backlog could be cleared.","Charlie McConalogue|Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Pippa Hackett|Super Junior Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine",Additional resources assigned to hearing appeals and a schedule for clearing the backlog of appeals to be heard.,|Letter|1,"Tara Flynn, Group HR Director",No,,False,,False,
66833,lobbying.ie/return/66833/cunningham-devlin-communications,Cunningham Devlin Communications,21/01/2021 11:11,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Energy and Natural Resources,"Engagement with government stakeholders concerned about public policy measures in relation to climate action about the contribution that the HubController automated energy management system could make in significantly reducing residential energy use for heating, saving households money and reducing emissions of greenhouse gases.","Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Mark Griffin|Secretary General|Department of Environment, Climate and Communications",Awareness and understanding among government stakeholders of the HubController automated energy management system its potential to significantly reduce greenhouse gas emissions and energy use from the residential housing stock.,|Email|6-10::|Submission|2-5,"Oliver Hynes, CEO of Hub Controls Ltd.",No,,False,,True,"HUB CONTROLS LIMITED|15 ELLENSBOROUGH LAWN KILTIPPER ROAD TALLAGHT DUBLIN 24 TALLAGHT, DUBLIN, D24X2R2, IRELAND|ollie@thehubcontroller.com|01 9010367"
