66837,lobbying.ie/return/66837/siptu---services-industrial-professional-trade-union,SIPTU - Services Industrial Professional Trade Union,21/01/2021 14:05,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Social Protection,Lobbying to stop the planned increase in State Pension Age,"Dara Calleary|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ollie Crowe|Senator|Seanad::Seán Sherlock|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Gary Gannon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Claire Kerrane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mary Lou McDonald|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Heather Humphreys|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",Repeal of the legislative provision for the pension age to rise to 67 in 2021 and 68 in 2028,|Email|2-5::|Phone call|2-5::|Virtual Meeting|2-5,Brian McGann + 108,No,,True,To campaign in their local constituency.,False,
66840,lobbying.ie/return/66840/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:16,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Trade,"Need to designate exporting businesses essential in light of COVID-19 developments, called on Government to support alternatives to the landbridge, renewed call for setting up an export credit agency and raised concerns about bank lending, or lack thereof, to businesses. Highlighted varying levels of Brexit preparedness among Irish businesses.","Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Robert Troy|Minister of State|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment",Ensure that exporters can continue to operate under different levels of COVID-19 restrictions. Ensure that the Government is prepared to potentially support direct shipping routes. The establishment of an export credit agency. Highlight and make Government aware of issues with lending that businesses are currently experiencing.,"Took place at a meeting of the Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment's Enterprise Forum|Virtual Meeting|1",Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
66843,lobbying.ie/return/66843/instinctif-partners-public-affairs-ireland,Instinctif Partners Public Affairs Ireland,21/01/2021 10:36,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,"Update on medicines supply, Brexit, Covid-19 and cost of medicines","Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cathal Crowe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Crowe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Gino Kenny|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Lahart|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Frances Black|Senator|Seanad::Lorraine Clifford-Lee|Senator|Seanad::Martin Conway|Senator|Seanad::Annie Hoey|Senator|Seanad::Seán Kyne|Senator|Seanad::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To update members of the Oireachtas Health Committee,|Email|1,DAVID DELANEY,No,,False,,True,"ALLIANCE OF MEDICINES FOR IRELAND COMPANY LIMITED BY GUARANTEE|70 SIR JOHN ROGERSON'S QUAY DUBLIN 2, DUBLIN, D02R296, IRELAND  |info@medicinesforireland.ie|+35315710938"
66848,lobbying.ie/return/66848/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:15,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Trade,"Raised concerned about lack of Brexit preparedness, particularly customs expertise, the need for the establishment of an export credit agency, raised concerns about bank lending and raised concerns about shipping capacity post-Brexit.",Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach,Make Government aware of the need to upskill workers in Brexit preparedness elements. To work towards establishing an export credit agency. To make the Government aware of issues with bank lending that businesses are experiencing. To make the Government aware that direct shipping routes may need to be supported.,Virtual meeting with the IEA National Council|Virtual Meeting|1,Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
