66945,lobbying.ie/return/66945/cityjet-designated-activity-company,CityJet Designated Activity Company,21/01/2021 16:12,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Taxation,Section 127B of the Taxes Consolidation Act 1997,"Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Cian O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Regina Doherty|Senator|Seanad::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Des Carville|Head of Unit|Department of Finance::Eoghan Murphy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mick Barry|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mairéad Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Steven Matthews|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John McGuinness|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jim O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neale Richmond|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Peadar Tóibín|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pat Casey|Senator|Seanad::Aidan Davitt|Senator|Seanad::Alice-Mary Higgins|Senator|Seanad::Marie Sherlock|Senator|Seanad","The Section is intended to prevent aircrew from avoiding tax. However, CityJet crews based outside of Ireland who are paying tax in the country where they live and work are also being required to pay tax in Ireland. CityJet's proposed amendment sought to confine the Section to untaxed income (i.e. its original intended purpose).","Emails to TDs, Senators, Oireachtas Committee and Department Official seeking requesting that amendment be included in Finance Bill 2020.|Email|11-20::Letter to Minister for Finance requesting that amendment be included in Finance Bill 2020|Letter|1::Calls with Minister Darragh O'Brien TD and Cian O'Callaghan TD to outline proposed amendment.|Phone call|2-5::Submission to Minister for Finance outlining rationale for proposed amendment.|Submission|1",Paul Brady,No,,False,,False,
