67170,lobbying.ie/return/67170/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:14,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Trade,"Submission to DETE Statement of Strategy 2021 - 2023: Called for stakeholder groups to continue and specifically called for the establishment of a business focused stakeholder group with DECC. Called for DETEs work to be in line with EU climate targets and to continue to attract sustainable FDI. Support remote working through expediating broadband roll out, establish digital marketing supports to business and introduce transitional tax relief to support the transition to remote working.","Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment","Continue and expand stakeholder groups in the coming years, particularly with regard to sustainability to ensure that businesses are included in the conversation and DETE's work is in line with climate targets, including attracting FDI and for DETE to keep remote working a central part of their strategy.",Our full submission to DETE's Statement of Strategy 2021 - 2023 is available on our website here: https://irishexporters.ie/submissions/iea-submission-dete-statement-of-strategy-2021-2023/|Submission|1,Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
