67311,lobbying.ie/return/67311/lens-media-limited,Lens Media Limited,22/01/2021 12:20,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,"To discuss plans for the development of a Media Park at Grange Castle Business Park, and issues relevant to the growth of the creative screen sector in Ireland. Grange Castle Media Park will be the first full-service media park on the island of Ireland that is designed to cater for both Irish and major international markets. It will generate between 1,200 and 1,500 jobs in the construction phase and, once complete, it will create at least 1,800 direct jobs and a further 1,800 ancillary jobs.","Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Eoin Ó Broin|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Francis Timmons|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Gary Gannon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Marie Sherlock|Senator|Seanad::Kenneth Egan|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Shirley O'Hara|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Vicki Casserly|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Shane Moynihan|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Niamh Smyth|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Madeleine Johansson|Councillor|South Dublin County Council::Ed Brophy|Special Adviser|Department of Finance","To raise awareness about plans for the development of a Media Park at Grange Castle Business Park, and issues relevant to the growth of the creative screen sector in Ireland.","To discuss plans for the development of a Media Park at Grange Castle Business Park, and issues relevant to the growth of the creative screen sector in Ireland. Grange Castle Media Park will be the first full-service media park on the island of Ireland that is designed to cater for both Irish and major international markets. It will generate between 1,200 and 1,500 jobs in the construction phase and, once complete, it will create approximately 1,800 direct jobs and a further 1,800 ancillary jobs.|Email|6-10::To discuss plans for the development of a Media Park at Grange Castle Business Park, and issues relevant to the growth of the creative screen sector in Ireland. Grange Castle Media Park will be the first full-service media park on the island of Ireland that is designed to cater for both Irish and major international markets. It will generate between 1,200 and 1,500 jobs in the construction phase and, once complete, it will create approximately 1,800 direct jobs and a further 1,800 ancillary jobs.|Virtual Meeting|6-10::To discuss plans for the development of a Media Park at Grange Castle Business Park, and issues relevant to the growth of the creative screen sector in Ireland. Grange Castle Media Park will be the first full-service media park on the island of Ireland that is designed to cater for both Irish and major international markets. It will generate between 1,200 and 1,500 jobs in the construction phase and, once complete, it will create approximately 1,800 direct jobs and a further 1,800 ancillary jobs.|Meeting|2-5","Alan Moloney, James Morris, Christopher Carlin, Matt Cooper, Gary Levinsohn",Yes,Martin Mackin|Senator|Seanad,False,,False,
