67327,lobbying.ie/return/67327/national-infertility-support-and-information-group,National Infertility Support and Information Group,21/01/2021 12:24,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Health,"NISIG is the only Irish charity supporting and advocacy on behalf of those experiencing fertility issues. NISIG is now part of a broader AHR Coalition Group formed in 2020 comprising LGBT Ireland, 221 Plus group, Equality for Children and the Rainbow Families Equality Network.  A main aim of the coalition is to ensure that equality is secured, and the human rights of children conceived using AHR, their intended parents and families are protected and advanced in legislation and policy.","Simon Harris|Minister|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science","To secure a meeting with the Minister of Further & Higher Education Simon Harris (former ex Minister of Health), to get his views and input on how to progress the proposed AHR legislation, particularly from the perspective of the human rights and equality of children conceived via AHR, their intended parents and families","Gillian Keegan, NISIG, was in email contact with Stephen Nolan from Minister Simon Harris's Wicklow Constituency Office in relation to organising a Virtual Meeting with Minister Simon Harris to discuss the proposed Assisted Human Reproduction Legislation.|Email|2-5::Gillian Keegan from NISIG had a virtual meeting with Minister of Further & Higher Education Simon Harris on December 11th 2020. We discussed how to progress the proposed AHR legislation with a key focus on the human rights and equality of children conceived via Assisted Human Reproduction, their intended parents and families. Also, discussed briefly was the just released Annual Child Protection report by Connor O' Mahony, special rapporteur on child protection, particularly in relation to the parental rights for families using surrogacy and other forms of assisted human reproduction.|Virtual Meeting|1",Gillian Keegan,No,,False,,False,
