67340,lobbying.ie/return/67340/migrant-rights-centre-ireland,Migrant Rights Centre Ireland,21/01/2021 15:08,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Agriculture,Creation of a Joint Sub-Committee to oversee reform of the meat processing sector,"Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Charlie McConalogue|Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Brophy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Carthy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Collins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul McAuliffe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael McNamara|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Murnane O'Connor|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Fergus O'Dowd|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Louise O'Reilly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pádraig O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Shanahan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Duncan Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","To include workers voices in the Agri-Food Strategy 2030 and Beef Taskforce::To make reforms that prevent bullying and discrimination::To review production levels and wider safety concerns of workers in meat processing factories::Introduction of mobility for all employment permit holders, similar to those for Critical Skills Permit Holders::Increase the capacity of the Health and Safety Authority and for them to develop sector specific guidelines::Creation of a Joint-Sub Committee to achieve the above","1 letter per representative (Minister Varadkar and Minister McConalogue) with slightly adjusted Dept-specific but cross cutting requests. An Taoiseach was only contacted via the grassroots action above.|Letter|2-5::Calls re setting up a Joint Sub-Committee to oversee reform of the meat processing sector|Phone call|2-5::2 tweets from Edel McGinley; 1 tweet from MRCI: directed at An Taoiseach, Minister Varadkar, and Minister McConalogue

