67707,lobbying.ie/return/67707/migrant-rights-centre-ireland,Migrant Rights Centre Ireland,21/01/2021 18:11,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Children and Youth Affairs,Introduction of permanent regularisation mechanism for undocumented children and young people in Ireland,"Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","Securing agreement and support from the Department of Children, Disability, Equality, Integration and Youth to lead on this issue.","Meeting with the Minister to discuss our recommendations to introduce a permanent  regularisation mechanism for undocumented children and young people in Ireland, for both those born here and born outside Ireland. Meeting was attended by staff from MRCI and young person from campaign group.|Conference Call|1::Meeting with TD to discuss the situation of undocumented children and young people growing up in Ireland, both born here and born abroad; highlighting the need for a permanent mechanism to be introduced; Meeting was attended by one staff member from MRCI.|Virtual Meeting|1",Mairéad McDevitt,No,,False,,False,
