67713,lobbying.ie/return/67713/federation-of-optometrists-and-dispensing-opticians,Federation of Optometrists and Dispensing Opticians,21/01/2021 09:56,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Our chair Garvan Mulligan wrote to Health Minister Donnelly TD on 5 October 2020 about protecting vision and eye health throughout the COVID-19 pandemic.  We were also in communication with Department of Health officials in November-December about ensuring that optical and hearing care practices were appropriately listed as essential healthcare services and thus able to remain operational to meet patients' needs throughout lockdown.,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health,"Prevention of visual and hearing impairment by enabling practices to remain operational to meet patients' vision, eye health and hearing needs, whilst deploying rigorous infection prevention and control procedures (including social distancing, PPE etc) to maintain patient, public and colleague safety.",|Email|2-5,"Mr Garvan Mulligan (Chair), Mr David Hewlett (Director)",No,,False,,False,
67714,lobbying.ie/return/67714/irish-society-for-the-prevention-of-cruelty-to-children,Irish Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children,21/01/2021 16:29,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Communications,"ISPCC's concerns about the possibility that, in December 2020, under the European Electronic Communications Code, tools currently being deployed to achieve the removal of child sexual abuse materials and to achieve other child protection objectives could become illegal.","Alan Dillon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Maria Walsh|MEP|European Parliament::Clare Daly|MEP|European Parliament",That MEPs would champion this with colleagues in the LIBE committee of the European Parliament and that these tools would not become illegal.,|Email|2-5,"John Church, CEO, ISPCC",No,,False,,False,
