67864,lobbying.ie/return/67864/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:33,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Representation to An Tánaiste regarding Review of Fair Deal pricing mechanism being outstanding three years after his deadline for completion when Minister for Health,"Leo Varadkar|An Tánaiste|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","To address with An Tánaiste that Fair Deal pricing review remains outstanding after it was recommended in July 2015 that the review should be completed within18 months. Furthermore, when Minister for Health, Minister Varadkar stipulated the review be completed 2017 and year-end 2020 it remains outstanding::To challenge and address An Tánaiste's comments that private and public nursing homes were incomparable because public nursing homes had residents of a higher dependency. The assertion is rejected by independent analyses undertaken assessing high-dependency care provided in nursing homes across the country",|Email|1::|Letter|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
