67972,lobbying.ie/return/67972/macra-na-feirme,Macra na Feirme,21/01/2021 18:41,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Budgetary matters,Macra na Feirme 2021 Budget - Transport,"Matt Carthy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Malcolm Byrne|Senator|Seanad::Heather Humphreys|Minister|Department of Social Protection::Anne Rabbitte|Minister of State|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Mattie McGrath|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Marian Harkin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Fergus O'Dowd|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Malcolm Noonan|Minister of State|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Alan Dillon|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Patrick Costello|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Charlie McConalogue|Minister|Department of Agriculture, Food and the Marine::John Brady|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Patricia Ryan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Éamon Ó Cuív|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Richard O'Donoghue|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Holly Cairns|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Violet Anne Wynne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Canney|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Peter Burke|Minister of State|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Mairéad Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Marc MacSharry|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Danny Healy-Rae|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Martin Browne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Robert Troy|Minister of State|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Catherine Connolly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Aindrias Moynihan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Paul Phelan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Niall Collins|Minister of State|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science::Thomas Gould|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Garvey|Senator|Seanad::Eugene Murphy|Senator|Seanad::Tim Lombard|Senator|Seanad","Increased provision of rural 44KW/50KW charging point::Through the Ireland Strategic Investment Fund (ISIF), a government fund would be created and used by the Industry to provide low-cost car insurance for young drivers that meet an appropriate and lower risk criterion for 2 years. This model is similar to the SCBI model of low-cost finance, where the risk is shared by the taxpayer and industry. Criteria- license type: full, age: 20-25, no penalty points, car size: 1.0l-1.6l, use of car-social, domestic and work commute only.::Free Travel for under 25s::Investment to return and upgrade bus-stops along rural routes including investment in modernisation and bus tracking for user interface (accessibility).::Investment in Phase 2 and 3 of the Western Rail Corridor.::Increase investment for upgrading of Rail platforms for accessibility.",|Email|2-5::|Virtual Meeting|1,"Thomas Duffy, National President; Denis Duggan, CEO; Derrie Dillon, Head of Advocacy, Membership & Policy, Sean Wallace, Munster Vice-President; Shane Quigley, Rural Youth Chair & Gillian Richardson, Ag Policy Officer",No,,False,,False,
