67978,lobbying.ie/return/67978/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:35,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Nursing Homes Ireland budget submission 2021 setting out requirements for nursing homes in 2021 budget,"Sean Fleming|Minister of State|Department of Finance::Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","To ensure fundamental issues in the funding of nursing home care are addressed in Budget 2021::To highlight the disparity in the funding of nursing home care and to advocate for further transparency from NTPF in its administration of the Nursing Home Support Scheme. Requirement for the Fair Deal scheme to encompass the reality of costs incurred to provide high-dependency, specialised care, with requirement to address the gross inequality in funding between HSE and private and voluntary nursing homes. Requirement to bring greater accountability to HSE nursing home expenditure::To question the value of the State diverting hundreds of millions of euro from a limited capital expenditure budget for capital works that will yield negligible additional capacity::To advocate for further extensions to Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme (TAPS) to support nursing homes in meeting the challenges presented by Covid-19, and to ensure that the costs associated with implementing the recommendations of the Nursing Homes Expert Panel are recognised as long-term expenditure for nursing homes::To put forward the need for commitments from insurers for a schedule of reductions that are required to support small and medium sized enterprises following a required reform to Irish insurance market",|Submission|1,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
