ort for funding for Horse Sport Ireland & the Sport Horse Industry|Letter|11-20::Submission to Minister MacConalogue outlining the Budget 2021 request for Horse Sport Ireland.|Submission|2-5::Letter outlining the details presented at the lobby day organised on 8th September 2020 in Buswells, including HSI Budget Submission, Economic Plan, and Strategic Plan 2019-2024.|Letter|2-5","Joe Reynolds, Chairman, Horse Sport Ireland, Ronan Murphy, CEO HSI, Barry O' Connor, HSI Economic Forum Chairman",No,,False,,False,
67988,lobbying.ie/return/67988/shannon-chamber,Shannon Chamber,20/01/2021 16:36,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Transport,Request to initiate the delivery of an alternative daily direct service from Rosslare to the port of Le Havre or Dieppe or Calais or Dunkirk or Zeebrugge to alleviate the potential lengthy delays at the ports on the English Channel for exports destined for European markets post Brexit.,"Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Hildegarde Naughton|Super Junior Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Violet Anne Wynne|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard O'Donoghue|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael McNamara|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe Carey|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","To put in place all the supports possible for the establishment of a direct daily service from Rosslare port to Mainland Europe (Le Havre, Dieppe, Calais or Dunkirk) and a daily return service from Europe.","Letters sent (via post and email to 2  Ministers on 26 Nov. 2020.  Copies of letters sent to 4 TDs on 26 Nov. 2020,|Letter|6-10","Helen Downes, CEO, Shannon Chamber i",No,,False,,False,
