68051,lobbying.ie/return/68051/prosper-fingal-clg,Prosper Fingal CLG,21/01/2021 10:14,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Health,"Following the announcement from Minister for Health Stephen Donnelly TD and Minister for Disability Anne Rabbitte TD that €10million would be made available to support the resumption of adult disability day services, Prosper Fingal's CEO emailed all elected representatives in Fingal, Dublin Bay North, Meath East and Meath West to raise  the concern that €10 million represents one tenth of the required funding for the resumption of national disability day services.","Helen McEntee|Minister|Department of Justice and Equality::Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Johnny Guirke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Denise Mitchell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Haughey|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Aodhán Ó Ríordáin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cian O'Callaghan|Councillor|Fingal County Council::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Louise O'Reilly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe O'Brien|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Damien English|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Duncan Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To address the matter of the insufficient budget allocation to the national disability sector for the resumption of day services.,"One email was sent to all elected representatives for Fingal, Dublin Bay North, Meath East and Meath West.  Replies were responded to accordingly.|Email|11-20","Pat Reen, CEO",No,,False,,False,
