68063,lobbying.ie/return/68063/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:37,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Budgetary matters,Engagement with Ministers and Elected Officials to ensure Budget 2021 prioritises people living in poverty and on a low income and that the measures taken are fair and equitable.,"Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Heather Humphreys|Minister|Department of Arts, Heritage and the Gaeltacht::Rónán Hession|Assistant Secretary|Department of Employment Affairs and Social Protection","That Budget 2021 would include SVP recommendations in regard to income adequacy, education, housing and homelessness and energy poverty, improving the supports and services for people on low incomes in Ireland.","Meeting the with Minister for Social Protection to introduce the Minister to the work of the Society and to outline our priorities for Budget 2021 in regard to income supports for lone parents who are working, benchmarking social welfare rates against the cost of a MESL, increase in the fuel allowance and income supports for younger and older children. 8th of October|Virtual Meeting|1::Meeting with the Minister for Finance as part of the Community and Voluntary Pillar to discuss Budget priorities regarding social welfare and income adequacy. 9th of September|Virtual Meeting|1",Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
