68079,lobbying.ie/return/68079/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:31,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Budgetary matters,"Engagement with Government Minister to ensure SVP's priorities and solutions regard housing, child poverty, direct provision, childcare, energy poverty and access to higher education are considered in the implementation of the Programme for Government","Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Simon Harris|Minister|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science::Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Marc Ó Cathasaigh|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",That the implementation of the Programme for Government would be poverty proofed. Improvements in the supports and services for the people SVP assist.,"Meeting with the Minister for Housing, Planning, Local Government and Heritage to introduce Minister to the work of the Society and outline our policy recommendations in regard to the Programme for Government, Rebuilding Ireland and the issue of rent arrears in the context of the Covid-19 crisis. Date 15th of September in the Custom House.|Meeting|1::Letter to the Minister for Further and Higher Education inviting him to meet with SVP to discuss our experience of supporting disadvantaged and second chance learners access education in the context of the proposed review of SUSI. Letter sent via email on the 6th of November.|Letter|1::Meeting with the Minister for Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth Affairs to introduce the Minister to the work of the Society and to outline our experience and policy recommendation in the areas of child poverty, early years and the National Childcare Scheme and Government White Paper on Direct Provision. Date 19th of November.|Meeting|1::Email to Minister Roderic O'Gorman, Deputy Hourigan and Deputy O'Cathasaigh regarding well-being indicators be developed and requesting that Public Finance Bill is amended so that budgetary decisions consider the impact they will have on levels of child poverty. Date 19th of November.|Email|1",Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
