68094,lobbying.ie/return/68094/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:32,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Children and Youth Affairs,Engagement with elected officials and senior civil servants as part of the National One Parent Family Alliance regarding the provision of supports for one-parent families impacted by the COVID-19 Pandemic,"Simon Harris|Minister|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science::Heather Humphreys|Minister|Department of Social Protection::Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth::Patrick Costello|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cathal Crowe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe Flaherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Kathleen Funchion|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John Paul Phelan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Sherlock|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mark Ward|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Brophy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Carthy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul McAuliffe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael McNamara|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Murnane O'Connor|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Fergus O'Dowd|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Louise O'Reilly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pádraig O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Shanahan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Duncan Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jackie Cahill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joan Collins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul Donnelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Charles Flanagan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Claire Kerrane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Denis Naughten|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Marc Ó Cathasaigh|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Éamon Ó Cuív|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","That the response to the COVID-19 pandemic considered the need of those parenting alone and included the provision of additional incomes supports, employment and childcare supports,  tenancy protections and rental supports, and measures to address energy poverty, food poverty and the digital divide as a result of school closures.","Joint NGO Submission on the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic and proposed measures to support lone parents during and after the lockdown sent to Minister Heather Humphreys on the 22nd of September.|Submission|1::Joint NGO Submission on the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic and proposed measures to support lone parents during and after the lockdown circulated to members of the COVID-19 Response Committee on the 14th of September.|Submission|1::Joint NGO Submission on the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic and proposed measures to support lone parents during and after the lockdown circulated to members of the Committee on Social Protection and the Committee on Children, Disability, Equality, Integration and Youth the 16th of September.|Submission|1::Joint NGO Submission on the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic and proposed measures to support lone parents during and after the lockdown sent to Minister Roderic O'Gorman on the 30th of September.|Submission|1::Letter to the Minister for Further and Higher Education inviting him to meet with the National One Parent Family Alliance to discuss the needs of lone parents seeking to access further and higher education during and after the COVID-19 pandemic. Letter sent via email on the 26th of November|Letter|1",Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
