68106,lobbying.ie/return/68106/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:30,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Housing,"Submission and presentation to the Committee on Housing, Local Government and Heritage on the findings of the joint SVP and Threshold research on the Housing Assistance Payment","Francis Noel Duffy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Thomas Gould|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Emer Higgins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Steven Matthews|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul McAuliffe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cian O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard O'Donoghue|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",That the operation and scope of the Housing Assistance Payment is reviewed in line with the needs of low income households and the current reality of the private rented market,Submission and presentation to the Committee on the 15th of December|Submission|1,Marcella Stakem,No,,False,,False,
68107,lobbying.ie/return/68107/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:08,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Meetings with Minister for Health and Officials regarding Covid19 in nursing homes and continued protection of residents and staff from the virus,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health,"Continued monitoring of guidance with regard to visits to nursing homes during Covid19::Vaccine rollout: Ensure residents and staff in nursing homes are immediate priority for vaccine rollout, given residents are the most suceptible to Covid19::TAPS: To advance requirement for Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme to encompass structures created to faciliate safe visiting during Covid19::Expert Panel: Impress upon the Department the essential requirement for the funding of measures recommended to be addressed, given they are not encompassed under the Nursing Home Support Scheme::Workforce Planning: Severe pressures upon workforce presented pre- and during Covid19 pandemic, with requirement presenting to address HCA shortage through the Ineligible Categories of Employment Listing and necessity for a medium to long-term workforce plan",|Virtual Meeting|2-5,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
68108,lobbying.ie/return/68108/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:28,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Social Protection,Bilateral meeting with the Department of Social Protection as part of the community and voluntary pillar,Tim Duggan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Employment Affairs and Social Protection,"Improvements in the supports and services for the people SVP assist, that the response to COVID-19 adequately supports low income households, that social welfare rates are benchmarked against the cost of the Minimum Essential Standard of Living, and that supports are available for working lone parents",Online meeting with department officials on the 24th of November|Virtual Meeting|1,Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
68109,lobbying.ie/return/68109/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:27,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Energy and Natural Resources,"Meeting with Senator Lynn Boylan to discuss the experience of SVP supporting people in energy poor homes, our policy submissions and research on energy poverty",Lynn Boylan|Senator|Seanad,"That SVP policy solutions regarding energy efficiency scheme criteria, minimum standards in the private rented sector, income supports for fuel poor homes and social tariffs are part of public policy.",Meeting on the 17th of December|Virtual Meeting|1,Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
