68114,lobbying.ie/return/68114/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:13,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Meeting between NHI Representatives and Representatives from Department of Health Social Care Division,Kathleen MacLellan|Assistant Secretary|Department of Health::Karen Greene|Chief Nursing Officer|Department of Health,Briefing on the implementation of the recommendations of the Nursing Homes Expert Panel::Update on development by Department of Health of safe staffing framework::Updated regarding implementation of the Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme and necessity to ensure it encompasses the reality of costs incurred to protect nursing home residents from Covid19::Department of Health to lead in implementation of workforce planning to ensure the critical shortalls in staffing within the nursing home and broader health services are addressed through a medium to long-term strategy::Engagement regarding serial testing of staff in nursing homes and requirement to ensure testing process is efficiently operated,|Virtual Meeting|2-5,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
68115,lobbying.ie/return/68115/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:26,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Social Protection,Meeting with Deputy Claire Kerrane regarding the establishment of a Commission on Social Welfare and the Social Welfare Bill,"Claire Kerrane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",That social welfare rates would be benchmarked against the cost of a MESL and that a review is carried out the eligibility criteria for the Fuel Allowance,Meeting to discuss benchmarking social welfare rates on the 25th of November|Virtual Meeting|1::Email including a request to amend to social welfare bill to include a review of the eligibility criteria for the Fuel Allowance on the 2nd of December.|Email|1,Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
