68117,lobbying.ie/return/68117/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:25,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Energy and Natural Resources,Submission to the Climate Action Committee on the Climate Action and Low-Carbon Development (Amendment) Bill 2020 in conjunction with Community Law and Mediation and the Jesuit Centre for Faith and Justice,"Réada Cronin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Christopher O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Whitmore|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","That the Bill would be amended to place a stronger obligation on the State to ensure that the specific needs of those experiencing poverty, inequality or social exclusion are taken into account when developing climate and sustainable development policies.",Submission circulated to members of the committee on 5th of November|Submission|1,Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
68118,lobbying.ie/return/68118/society-of-st-vincent-de-paul,Society of St. Vincent de Paul,20/01/2021 19:23,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Finance,"Submission to the  Committee on Finance, Expenditure and Public Reform and Taoiseach on the Consumer Credit (Amendment) Bill 2018","Mick Barry|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bernard Durkan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Mairéad Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Steven Matthews|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John McGuinness|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jim O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neale Richmond|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Peadar Tóibín|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",That a interest rate restriction in introduced for licenced moneylenders that lowers the cost of credit for low income households,Submission circulated to members of the committee via clerk on 24th of November|Submission|1,Tricia Keilthy,No,,False,,False,
