68153,lobbying.ie/return/68153/irish-penal-reform-trust,Irish Penal Reform Trust,21/01/2021 11:39,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Justice and Equality,Submission to Oireachtas Special Committee on COVID-19 Response,"Michael McNamara|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Brophy|Minister of State for the Diaspora and Overseas Development Aid|Department of Foreign Affairs::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Carroll MacNeill|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Carthy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Michael Collins|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Paul McAuliffe|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Murnane O'Connor|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Fergus O'Dowd|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Louise O'Reilly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pádraig O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matt Shanahan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Duncan Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",Minimise the use of imprisonment as a sanction during a pandemic::Prioritise social measures over penal measures during a pandemic::Ensure equal access to justice in remote court hearings::Strengthen inspection and oversight of all places of detention::Advocate for human rights assessment of measures introduced in response to emergency situations::Legislate to protect against the use of prolonged solitary confinement in prison,"IPRT was invited by the Oireachtas Special Committee on COVID-19 Response to make a submission on how the State’s legislative framework contributed to an effective response to the current crisis, and proposals for improvements and reforms.|Submission|1","Fíona Ní Chinnéide, Executive Director",No,,False,,False,
68154,lobbying.ie/return/68154/community-law--mediation,Community Law & Mediation,20/01/2021 22:29,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Housing,"Submission to the Department of Housing, Local Government & Heritage in relation to its Statement of Strategy","Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage","Department prioritises inclusion of a right to housing in the Constitution; provision of a stable, sustainable, culturally appropriate supply of good quality housing; and a commitment to review the eligibility and allocation systems in place for social housing across local authorities and to ensuring access to culturally appropriate accommodation",|Submission|1,Rose Wall,No,,False,,False,
