68156,lobbying.ie/return/68156/irish-penal-reform-trust,Irish Penal Reform Trust,20/01/2021 23:53,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Justice and Equality,Progress in the Penal System 2020,Oonagh McPhillips|Deputy Secretary|Department of Justice and Equality,Letter of invitation to the Secretary General of the Department of Justice to deliver keynote address,"Letter of invitation to the Secretary General of the Department of Justice to deliver the keynote address at the January 2021 launch of IPRT's new report, 'Progress in the Penal System: 2020'.|Letter|1","Fíona Ní Chinnéide, Executive Director",No,,False,,False,
68157,lobbying.ie/return/68157/environmental-pillar,Environmental Pillar,20/01/2021 22:47,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Marine,"Heads of the Marine Planning and Development Management Bill - raised key concerns including: key EU Directive and Aarhus Convention considerations; protection of the marine environment and biodiversity in relation to the development of renewable energy infrastructure projects; nature of jobs which would be realised locally and circular economy concerns; constitutional compliance of the Heads of Bill, as well as the Spatial Planning Directive. Highlighted importance of pre-legislative scrutiny.","Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad::Cian O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Steven Matthews|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Francis Noel Duffy|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","Ensure the Marine Planning and Development Bill protects and enhances marine biodiversity; ensure there are adequate provisions for public participation and debate in the legislative process in relation to this Bill, which will have far-reaching impacts for communities throughout the country.",|Email|11-20::|Phone call|2-5::|Informal communication|2-5,Attracta Uí Bhroin,No,,False,,False,
