68161,lobbying.ie/return/68161/environmental-pillar,Environmental Pillar,20/01/2021 22:56,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,"Foreign Affairs ","Notified Government of the detention of environmental rights activist in Belarus, Ms Sukihy. Sought immediate engagement of Irish authorities to clarify details surrounding her detention and secure her release, noting concerns in relation to the Aarhus Convention and human rights treaties protecting environmental defenders and civil society leaders.",Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach::Simon Coveney|Minister|Department of Foreign Affairs,"Secure the release of an environmental rights defender who was detained in Belarus, in line with international protections for activists and civil society leaders.",Letter sent by email.|Letter|1,Karen Ciesielski,No,,False,,False,
