68167,lobbying.ie/return/68167/irish-penal-reform-trust,Irish Penal Reform Trust,20/01/2021 23:03,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Justice and Equality,Priority penal reform issues,Helen McEntee|Minister|Department of Justice,Strengthen accountability and oversight of prisons through timely publication of monitoring reports::Discuss measures to minimise the impact of COVID-19 on the prison system and meet human rights obligations::Ensure implementation of the Parole Act 2019 meets the rights and needs of all stakeholders,"Letter to Minister for Justice seeking a meeting to discuss three specific areas: (i) prisons inspections, monitoring, and complaints; (ii) Covid-19 and the criminal justice sector; and (iii) implementation of the Parole Act 2019.|Letter|1","Fíona Ní Chinnéide, Executive Director",No,,False,,False,
68168,lobbying.ie/return/68168/irish-environmental-network,Irish Environmental Network,20/01/2021 23:04,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Environment,"Heads of Housing Development and Planning Bill, 2019: Highlighted need to allow environmental non-governmental organisations to provide input to the pre-legislative process.",Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad,"Ensure the legislative process encourages public participation and involves rich, comprehensive debate to fully explore all issues in relation to this Bill.",|Email|1,Attracta Uí Bhroin,No,,False,,False,
