68172,lobbying.ie/return/68172/irish-environmental-network,Irish Environmental Network,20/01/2021 23:22,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Environment,Heads of Water Environment (Extraction) Bill: Highlighted that the EU Commission had issued a Reasoned Opinion against Ireland in respect of failures under the EU Water Framework Directive and the potential implications for Ireland's approach to resolving deficiencies under the Directive and the importance of discussing these issues during pre-legislative scrutiny.,"Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad",Ensure the Bill is in compliance with EU environmental laws.,|Email|2-5::|Informal communication|2-5,Attracta Uí Bhroin,No,,False,,False,
68173,lobbying.ie/return/68173/image-learning-and-development-training-network-company-limited-by-guarantee-ta-habic,"Image Learning and Development Training Network, company Limited by Guarantee T/A HABIC",20/01/2021 23:22,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Reopening of the Personal Grooming Industry,"Declan Hughes|Assistant Secretary|Department of Business, Enterprise and Innovation",Meeting to discuss the reopening of the personal grooming industry and the issue that are impacting the industry.,|Virtual Meeting|1,Margaret O'Rourke Doherty,No,,False,,False,
68174,lobbying.ie/return/68174/image-learning-and-development-training-network-company-limited-by-guarantee-ta-habic,"Image Learning and Development Training Network, company Limited by Guarantee T/A HABIC",20/01/2021 23:26,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Reopening of the Personal Grooming and Issues around COVID-19,,That salon can open in advance of the 2nd of December as they were all fully booked on the 1st of December. that our concerns around COVID-19 would be taken on board.,,Margaret O'Rourke Doherty,No,,False,,False,
68175,lobbying.ie/return/68175/image-learning-and-development-training-network-company-limited-by-guarantee-ta-habic,"Image Learning and Development Training Network, company Limited by Guarantee T/A HABIC",20/01/2021 23:35,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,"Lobbied to have the 9% Vat rate extended to both the beauty and hair industry, justification was requested as to why the beauty industry has not been granted the 9% VAT rate in the budget alongside hairdressing. Additional clarification was requested upon receipt of the rationale given.","Declan Hughes|Assistant Secretary|Department of Business, Enterprise and Innovation::Pascal Dohoghue|Minister|Department of Finance::Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Robert Watt|Secretary General|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Damien English|Minister of State|Department of Housing, Planning and Local Government::Leo Varadkar|Minister|Department of Defence::Leo Varadkar|An Tánaiste|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::John McGuinness|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Maria Walsh|MEP|European Parliament::Frank Feighan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Frank Feighan|Minister of State|Department of Health::Robert Troy|Minister of State|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Kieran O'Donnell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Derek Moran|Secretary General|Department of Finance::Pearse Doherty|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Ed Brophy|Special Adviser|Department of Finance","Reduction and Inclusion of the  9% Vat rate for the beauty industry, the 9% Vat rate should be extended to include both the hair and beauty services as per the NACE 9602 classification.",Emails to outline various aspects of information and EU classifications that we believe should justify extension of the VAT rate to the beauty industry in Ireland.|Email|2-5::Phone calls with Department of Finance to understand the rationale and to seek an adjustment and extension of the lowered 9% Vat to included the beauty industry.|Phone call|2-5,Margaret O'Rourke Doherty,No,,False,,False,
68176,lobbying.ie/return/68176/irish-penal-reform-trust,Irish Penal Reform Trust,20/01/2021 23:47,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,"Mental health, addictions and imprisonment",Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Frances Black|Senator|Seanad,"Support the Government commitment to establish a Task Force on mental health, addictions and imprisonment::Diversion of people with mental illness away from the criminal justice system to appropriate treatment and supports::Improve access to mental health treatment and services in the community through resourcing and legislative change.","Introductory letters, noting IPRT's concerns regarding the impact of Covid-19 on mental health of prisoners, and welcoming Government commitments to improving approaches to mental health in the criminal justice system.|Letter|2-5","Fíona Ní Chinnéide, Executive Director",No,,False,,False,
68177,lobbying.ie/return/68177/irish-environmental-network,Irish Environmental Network,20/01/2021 23:44,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Environment,Transboundary Consultation on Sizewell C Nuclear Power Plant: Highlighted key concerns and potential implications of transboundary impacts of the development of the nuclear power plant on public health and the environment in Ireland.,"David Healy|Councillor|Fingal County Council::Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Declan Bree|Councillor|Sligo County Council::Colette Connolly|Councillor|Galway City Council",Ensure that Ireland's rights are upheld under international environmental laws with regard to consultation and that any developments in relation to the Sizewell C Nuclear Plant are analysed with regard to the critical environmental and public health risks to Ireland.,|Email|2-5,Attracta Uí Bhroin,No,,False,,False,
68178,lobbying.ie/return/68178/irish-environmental-network,Irish Environmental Network,21/01/2021 12:48,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Environment,"Climate Action and Low Carbon Development (Amendment) Bill 2020: Highlighted issues with regard to public participation in respect of the Aarhus Convention to members of the Joint Oireachtas Committee on Climate Action, citing need for adequate timeframes and the need to hear from a range of expert witnesses as part of the pre-legislative scrutiny process; suggested topics to cover in support of the Aarhus Convention.","Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad::Pauline O'Reilly|Senator|Seanad::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Whitmore|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alice-Mary Higgins|Senator|Seanad::Réada Cronin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Lynn Boylan|Senator|Seanad::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Timmy Dooley|Senator|Seanad::John McGahon|Senator|Seanad::Christopher O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",Ensure climate action is underpinned by robust legislation and policies.,|Email|6-10::|Phone call|2-5::|Email|2-5,Attracta Uí Bhroin,No,,False,,False,
