68303,lobbying.ie/return/68303/christine-buckley-centre-for-education-and-support-clg,Christine Buckley Centre for Education and Support CLG,21/01/2021 14:58,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Justice and Equality,Commission of Inquiry into Mother and Baby Homes and Certain Related Matters: The Christine Buckley Centre among other agencies working together contacted all depts of the Oireachtas on 5th October and released a press statement in light of the upcoming report release. They launched the Facing The Future Together Report to highlight issues and identified 5 key asks for all Survivors. Our Co-Founder was interviewed on the launch via webinar 9th October and via press.,"Roderic O'Gorman|Minister|Department of Children, Equality, Disability, Integration and Youth",5 Key Asks for All Survivors: 1. Global Supports for Survivors based outside Ireland. 2. Services for Families- Accessible Counselling. 3. Health Amendment Act Health Card for All Survivors. 4. Advocacy Support including Public Services with Strong links to Support Services. 5. Trauma Informed Training for All Staff working in customer facing roles on how to identify Survivors and Respond to their unique needs.::From the Christine Buckley Centre to also highlight the need for increased resources and supports to be given to Frontline services who already working directly with Survivors.,"After the email was sent on the 5th October a webinar was held on 9th October to launch the Facing the Future Together Report and invites were sent to Members of the Oireachtas, Press and Survivors networks in Ireland. After this panelists from the groups spoke to the press in following weeks. The Oireachtas Members received PDF versions on 5th October and printed hardcopies in the following weeks.|Event / Reception|51-100","Carmel McDonnell Byrne Co-Founder, Manager Nóra Dempsey and Chairperson of the Board Donal Buckley",No,,False,,False,
68304,lobbying.ie/return/68304/irish-rural-link-co-operative-society-limited,Irish Rural Link Co-Operative Society Limited,21/01/2021 11:02,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Community,Meeting with Deputy Holly Cairns as Social Democrats spokesperson for Rural development.,"Holly Cairns|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",Meeting was to highlight the work of Irish Rural Link and discuss some of the challenges and opportunities for rural areas in the current climate.  Also to arrange a meeting with the wider Social Democrats party.,|Virtual Meeting|1,Seamus Boland Sinead Dooley Louise Lennon,No,,False,,False,
