68306,lobbying.ie/return/68306/gerard-howlin,Gerard Howlin,21/01/2021 19:09,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Finance,"To lobby for the policy objectives of ILCU as set out in its 2020 Vision document and its detailed policy documents on funding for social housing, lending to SMEs and provision of micro-credit. To lobby for delivery of commitments to credit unions in the Programme for Government. To provide information to Oireachtas members on credit union issues of interest to them.","Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Sean Fleming|Minister of State|Department of Finance::Frances Fitzgerald|MEP|European Parliament::Richard O'Donoghue|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Eoin Ó Broin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","To deliver on the policy objectives of ILCU as set out in its 2020 Vision document and its detailed policy documents on funding for social housing, lending to SMEs and provision of micro-credit. To achieve delivery on commitments to credit unions in the Programme for Government. To provide information to Oireachtas members on credit union issues of interest to them.::To advance implementation of ILCU's policy objectives by government and Oireachtas::To seek reversal of proposed increases in the Industrial Levy on credit unions::To seek a review of credit union legislation","Calls with Ministers, Oireachtas members and MEP|Phone call|2-5::emails to Oireachtas members|Email|2-5",Gerard Howlin,Yes,Gerard Howlin|Special Adviser|Department of the Taoiseach,True,To make politicians aware of credit union issues,True,"Irish League of Credit Unions|33-41 Lower Mount Street, Dublin 2|info@creditunion.ie|+353 1 614-6700"
