68313,lobbying.ie/return/68313/prosper-meath-clg,Prosper Meath CLG,21/01/2021 11:15,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Health,"Following the announcement from Minister for Health Stephen Donnelly TD and Minister for Disability Anne Rabbitte TD that €10million would be made available to support the resumption of adult disability day services, Prosper Meath's CEO emailed all elected representatives in Meath East, Meath West, Fingal, and Dublin Bay North to raise the concern that €10 million represents one tenth of the required funding for the resumption of national disability day services.","Louise O'Reilly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe O'Brien|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Damien English|Minister of State|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment::Duncan Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Johnny Guirke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Helen McEntee|Minister|Department of Justice::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach::Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Denise Mitchell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Seán Haughey|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Aodhán Ó Ríordáin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cian O'Callaghan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To address the matter of the insufficient budget allocation to the national disability sector for the resumption of day services.,"One email was sent to all elected representatives for Fingal, Dublin
Bay North, Meath East and Meath West. Replies were responded to
accordingly.|Email|11-20","Pat Reen, CEO",No,,False,,False,
