68466,lobbying.ie/return/68466/engineers-ireland,Engineers Ireland,21/01/2021 14:00,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Briefings: State of Ireland Report 2020,"William Beausang|Assistant Secretary|Department of Further and Higher Education, Innovation and Science::Mark Griffin|Secretary General|Department of Environment, Climate and Communications::Orlaigh Quinn|Secretary General|Department of Business, Enterprise and Innovation::Maria Graham|Assistant Secretary|Department of Housing, Planning and Local Government::Ronnie Downes|Assistant Secretary|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Ray O'Leary|Assistant Secretary|Department of Transport, Tourism and Sport","Briefings were offered by Engineers Ireland, to ensure senior Officials in relevant Government departments were informed about our planned 2020 publication 'State of Ireland 2020 - Engineering a Green and Digital Recovery'.::The State of Ireland report is Engineers Ireland’s annual independent assessment of Ireland’s infrastructure and technology. Each year, an advisory group of engineers and other professionals develop recommendations for public policy.  The 2020 document states that Ireland’s recovery will be green and digital, driven by investments in infrastructure, technology and education.","Emails offering a meeting or briefing, with Engineers Ireland about our report, were sent to the Departmental officials below.|Email|6-10::Note that as a result of this email contact, a meeting was undertaken with Mr W. Beausang, by Dr Richard Manton, our Policy Officer in Engineers Ireland.|Meeting|1","Caroline Spillane, Director General of Engineers Ireland",No,,False,,False,
