68473,lobbying.ie/return/68473/shannon-chamber,Shannon Chamber,21/01/2021 14:10,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Budgetary matters,Chambers Ireland Budget 2021 Submission,Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance::Ed Brophy|Special Adviser|Department of Finance,"Discuss the Chambers Ireland Budget 2021 submission, highlighting both our budgetary and legislative priorities under 5 of the SDGs.   The intended results were to discuss and underline how best to continue to support jobs and businesses, infrastructure spending and investment in the period ahead, how we can help town centres, remote working, supporting companies to scale, driving more balanced regional development, and housing.",A participant in Chambers Ireland's virtual meeting on 2 Oct. 2020|Virtual Meeting|1,"Helen Downes, CEO, Shannon Chamber",No,,False,,False,
