68483,lobbying.ie/return/68483/sse-plc,SSE plc,21/01/2021 15:27,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Energy and Natural Resources,Meeting with Eamon Ryan to discuss Ireland’s Climate Action objectives.,"Eamon Ryan|Minister|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport::Paul Kenny|Special Adviser|Department of Climate Action, Communication Networks and Transport","SSE welcomed the Programme for Government and particularly the increase in offshore wind 2030 ambitions from 3.5GW to 5GW, highlighting to opportunity for a green recovery from Covid-19. SSE discussed with attendees the opportunity for offshore wind in the delivery of Ireland's climate action objectives and  the role of our own investments, including Arklow Bank Phase 2, which can deliver the first offshore wind farm of scale by 2025.::. SSE also raised their recent partnership with An Post to finance energy efficiency measures, highlighting how it is an example of how SSE can support the government in achieving their ambitions for retrofit by 2030, and highlighted the need for “always-on” grants, which will be needed to achieve the Government’s ambitions.",|Virtual Meeting|1,"Klair Neenan, Stephen Wheeler, Barry Kilcline",No,,False,,False,
