68488,lobbying.ie/return/68488/engineers-ireland,Engineers Ireland,21/01/2021 16:56,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,Dáil and Seanad Éireann members: Information & link to the State of Ireland 2020 Report,,"To provide information to our elected officials including the link to our 'State of Ireland Report 2020 - Engineering a Green and Digital Recovery'. We felt the report would be useful for them in their roles as policymakers and thought leaders.::The State of Ireland 2020 is the tenth annual instalment in a series examining the state of critical sectors of our country’s built environment. The report advocates for Ireland’s recovery to be green and digital, driven by investments in infrastructure, technology and education. It is informed by a dedicated advisory group of engineers and other professionals.::The report, publicly available, outlines a set of recommendations that will help the Irish economy to recover by tackling the challenges and embracing the opportunities arising from climate change, digitalisation and Brexit.::The dedicated advisory group to the Report, was chaired by our President Maurice Buckley, C Eng. (2020/21).",,"Caroline Spillane, Director General of Engineers Ireland.",No,,False,,False,
68489,lobbying.ie/return/68489/an-post,An Post,21/01/2021 14:28,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Communications,Application of Union Customs Code for Customs 2020 project and Brexit,Florance Carey|Assistant Secretaries or Equivalent Grades|The Office of the Revenue Commissioners,Discussion on the development of IT systems and the application of Union Customs Code for Customs 2020 project and for Brexit,|Meeting|1,"Cyril McGrane, Head of International Trade, An Post",No,,False,,False,
68490,lobbying.ie/return/68490/sse-plc,SSE plc,21/01/2021 15:26,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Energy and Natural Resources,Meeting with Christopher O'Sullivan TD to give an overview of Arklow Bank Wind Farm.,"Christopher O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","Give an overview to the Deputy on SSE's plans at Arklow Bank, convey the positive impact offshore wind can have in driving investment in support of Ireland's recovery from COVID-19, and outline the need for the offshore wind to be established in Ireland with first project operational approximately 2025.",|Virtual Meeting|1,Louise Glennon,No,,False,,False,
