68495,lobbying.ie/return/68495/national-irish-safety-organisation,National Irish Safety Organisation,21/01/2021 14:33,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Employment,Reducing Employer Liability Insurance Claim Costs; Working Party review of Health and Safety; Separation of Ministers for Occupational Safety; Public sector promotion of health and safety; NISO Representation on Departmental Working Group; NISO representation on HSA Board,"Damien English|Minister of State|Department of Enterprise, Trade and Employment",Reducing Employer Liability Insurance Claim Costs: Simply reducing the compensation levels was not enough but all the costs surrounding the compensation also needs to be reviewed. However the promotion of health and safety was key to the prevention of accidents in the first case.::Working Party review of Health and Safety: Now time for another working party to review health and safety for the next 25 / 30 years.::Separation of Ministers for Occupational Safety: The separation of responsibility for farm safety from the current Department to a different Minister. Request that this be reconsidered owing to the potential for differing priorities.::Public sector promotion of health and safety: Public bodies should be taking the lead when it comes to showcasing occupational health and safety promotion. Minister asked to assist.::NISO representation on Departmental Working Group: NISO wishes to be represented on the Departmental Working Group::NISO representation on HSA Board: NISO wishes to be represented on the HSA Board.,|Virtual Meeting|1,Harry Galvin,No,,False,,False,
