68561,lobbying.ie/return/68561/sightsavers-ireland,Sightsavers Ireland,21/01/2021 14:57,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,"Foreign Affairs ","In 2018, Ireland ratified the United Nations Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (CRPD), and in December 2020 it will have its first vote in the elections for members of the committee that oversees this treaty. The elections will take place at the Conference of States Parties to the CRPD in New York, and Ciara Smullen sort Simon Coveney's support in asking that votes in the election to improve the diversity and gender balance on the committee.",Simon Coveney|Minister|Department of Foreign Affairs,"For Minister for Foreign Affairs, Simon Coveney TD to cast votes at the UN on the membership of the Rights of Persons with Disability (CRPD) committee in December to ensure that women, people with diverse disability types and people from low and middle income countries are fairly represented.","Letter sent to Simon Coveney in October 2020 requesting that Ireland casts its votes in December to ensure that women, people with diverse disability types and people from low and middle income countries are fairly represented.|Letter|1",Ciara Smullen,No,,False,,False,
