68565,lobbying.ie/return/68565/irish-exporters-association,Irish Exporters Association,21/01/2021 15:12,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Trade,"Meeting with IEA Council: Called for supports to upskill workers in Brexit preparedness matters, raised concerns about capacity to directly ship to the EU, raised concerns about bank lending to businesses at present, asked for an update on the EU's work on tax and asked for information on potential Covid-19 testing at airports.",Thomas Byrne|Minister of State|Department of the Taoiseach,"Government to assess the need to roll out further Brexit preparedness training. To also assess direct shipping capacity available post-Brexit, looking into issues with bank lending for businesses, update members of EU tax proposals and to get views on potentially Covid-19 testing at Irish airports.",Virtual meeting with the IEA National Council|Virtual Meeting|1,Simon McKeever,No,,False,,False,
