68603,lobbying.ie/return/68603/charities-institute-ireland,Charities Institute Ireland,21/01/2021 15:16,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Public Expenditure and Reform,A number of  issues and challenges were raised with several members in regards to the current process of The National Lottery Good Cause funding.,Michael McGrath|Minister|Department of Public Expenditure and Reform::Joe O'Brien|Minister of State|Department of Rural and Community Development,"Given that any changes to the method and manner of the distribution of Good Causes funding are issues of policy for the Government, Cii would appreciate the opportunity to meet with you as Minister responsible for this area alongside a number of our members so we can outline the main challenges that charities face in applying for Good Causes funding as well as discussing potential improvements to the process.",|Email|1,Liz Hughes,No,,False,,False,
