68614,lobbying.ie/return/68614/mcdonalds-restaurants-of-ireland-limited,McDonald's Restaurants of Ireland Limited,21/01/2021 15:23,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Economic Development and Industry,"Meetings with the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Simon Coveney and Tánaiste & Minister for Enterprise, Trade and Employment, Leo Varadkar, on the business environment during the pandemic and Brexit.","Leo Varadkar|An Tánaiste|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Simon Coveney|Minister|Department of Foreign Affairs","To brief both Ministers on McDonald’s operations in Ireland, its enhanced Covid-19 safety measures and to gain a better understanding of the wider business environment during the pandemic. McDonald’s also intended to get an update from both Ministers on the implications of Brexit for businesses in the event of a no-deal scenario.",|Virtual Meeting|2-5,"Simon Tiernan, Head of Communications, McDonald’s Ireland, Paul Pomroy, Chief Executive Office, McDonald’s UK & Ireland, Beth Hart, VP Supply Chain and Brand Trust, McDonald’s UK & Ireland",No,,False,,False,
68615,lobbying.ie/return/68615/financial-justice-ireland,Financial Justice Ireland,21/01/2021 15:24,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Finance,We wrote to the Minister for Finance to follow up on previous correspondence calling for permanent debt cancellation for developing countries in the light of the Covid-19 epidemic,Paschal Donohoe|Minister|Department of Finance,"We called on the Irish government to use its influence to support the call for: - an immediate and permanent cancellation of all principal, interest and charges for the remainder of 2020 for all countries in need, and most urgently for PRGT and IDA countries. - to push for extension of this offer to payments due on multilateral debt in 2020, including those of the IMF and World Bank (WB).",We arranged an email campaign targeting the Minister for Finance highlighting the global week of action on debt cancellation in the light of COVID|Email|2-5,Maeve Bateman,No,,False,"Email the Minister for Finance asking him to: (1) Cancel all debt payments for countries suffering from the economic impacts of coronavirus, due in 2020.  (2) Help countries in trouble to restructure their debt rather than bailing out lenders. (3) Ensure new finance, granted to tackle the coronavirus, does not create more debt.",False,
