68662,lobbying.ie/return/68662/nursing-homes-ireland,Nursing Homes Ireland,21/01/2021 17:02,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Health,Continued engagement and briefing regarding the Covid19 situation in nursing homes.,Stephen Donnelly|Minister|Department of Health::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health,"Discussions regarding the requirement for continued engagement between public health and nursing homes at regional level to ensure timely access to community support, where required.::Representation regarding the essential importance of serial testing of staff in nursing homes to enable early detection of Covid19 and support the management of any prospective outbreak, with NHI advancing move from every two weeks to minimum once a week.::Advancement for Covid19 Nursing Homes Expert Panel recommendations to be implemented by matter of priority to establish greater supports for nursing homes in providing specialised care.::Engagement regarding operation of the Covid19 Temporary Assistance Payment Scheme in meeting the substantive costs associated with preventing and managing the pandemic, with NHI advancing requirement for costs entailed to develop purpose-built visiting facilities to be encompassed under TAPS.::Representations regarding requirement to extend the Ineligible Categories of Employment Listing to include Healthcare Assistants, to meet substantive shortfall across nursing home sector and broader healthcare services to fill HCA roles.",|Email|2-5,"Tadhg Daly, NHI CEO",No,,False,,False,
