68668,lobbying.ie/return/68668/esb,ESB,21/01/2021 16:32,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Legislation,Energy and Natural Resources,"A range of engagements relating to the use of hybrid connections for embedded generation - combining offshore wind with existing thermal generation stations - to accelerate the delivery of offshore wind to meet the Programme for Government targets of 5,000MW by 2030.  These include submission of a proposal on items to consider in relation to the MPDM Bill, in addition to separate engagements emphasising the criticality of the approach and the need for a speedy implementation of the MPDM Bill.","Steven Matthews|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Matthew Collins|Assistant Secretary|Department of Environment, Climate and Communications",Seek support from DECC of proposals that would facilitate inclusion of hybrid connections for offshore generation as a means to fast-track offshore wind connections,"Engagements involved:
Jim Dollard, Executive Director Generation & Trading, ESB;
Donal Phelan, Asset Manager, Generation & Trading, ESB;
Peter O’Shea, Head of Corporate & Regulatory Affairs, ESB;
Seán Murphy, Public Affairs Manager, ESB.

Engagements included: 
–	Skype on 1/12/2020
–	Letter to JOC dated 10th December 2020
–	Subsequent emails circulating letter on 15th/16th  Dec submitted to Chair & Members of Housing, Local Government & Heritage Committee and Committee on Climate Action|Letter|1::|Virtual Meeting|1::|Email|2-5","Jim Dollard, Executive Director Generation & Trading, ESB",No,,False,,False,
