68732,lobbying.ie/return/68732/dyslexia-association-of-ireland,Dyslexia Association of Ireland,21/01/2021 16:50,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Education and Training,"Meeting to highlight issues impacting on students with dyslexia within the school system. Topics included the need for mandatory teacher training on dyslexia, a specialist dyslexia teacher role, the right to identification/assessment and the impact of this on mental health, the need for better access and funding for assistive technology, and the need for change in our examinations system to provide choice via a wider range of assessment methods .",Josepha Madigan|Minister of State|Department of Education,"Create awareness of the issues with Minister Madigan and her officials, and seek commitments to address these issues in order to make our education system more dyslexia friendly.",Meeting at the Dept. of Education in Marlborough St. on October 8|Meeting|1,Rosie Bissett,No,,False,,False,
