68803,lobbying.ie/return/68803/age-action,Age Action,21/01/2021 17:30,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Budgetary matters,"Budget 2021 priorities issues for Age Action -the creation of an office for a Commissioner on Ageing, a new National Digital Strategy with adequate supports for continuous learning, pension adequacy and reform, a digital allowance, rights based statutory home care scheme, commencement of the Assisted Decision Making Act and funding to fully operate the Decision Support Service","Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Kelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Helen McEntee|Minister|Department of Justice::Mary Butler|Minister of State|Department of Health::Darragh O'Brien|Minister|Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage::Micheál Martin|An Taoiseach|Department of the Taoiseach",TD aware of issues around Age Action's Budget 2021 priorities and give consideration to supporting the 'asks'  in Budget 2021.,Pre-Budget Submission - Life with Dignity in Older Age - circulated to members of the Oireachtas.|Submission|1,Celine Clarke,No,,False,,False,
68804,lobbying.ie/return/68804/engineers-ireland,Engineers Ireland,21/01/2021 17:31,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Public policy or programme,Environment,Invitations to our National Conference 2020: Engineering Climate Action,"Richard Bruton|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Réada Cronin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Cormac Devlin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Farrell|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Brian Leddin|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Darren O'Rourke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Christopher O'Sullivan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Bríd Smith|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Jennifer Whitmore|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas","Our 2020 National Conference was on the theme of Engineering Climate Action, Solutions to combat climate change in Ireland. We sent guest invitations to members of the Select Committee on Climate Action (Oireachtas) to attend, as we felt it might be a useful 'solutions' focused learning event for them. Our conference, which was primarily for our member engineers, had both national and international speakers.","Our National Conference 2020 took place online on 21 October. The guest invites went by email to the Select Committee.|Email|6-10::Some social media took place (from us) post our National Conference relating to an online article in the Sunday Business Post (opinion piece 29 October), written by our President Maurice Buckley (in the context of him being our President & representing our membership) & relating to actions to mitigate climate change and also what the Government's approach should be.  The article stated that engineers have a critical role to play in Ireland’s transition to a low-carbon energy model and now is the opportune time to invest in public infrastructure to drive the green recovery. Some general social media took place from us to draw attention to the article - with none directed at any one political representative.|Social Media|2-5","Anne Marie Clarke, Press and Events Officer at Engineers Ireland",No,,False,,False,
68805,lobbying.ie/return/68805/irish-skin-foundation,Irish Skin Foundation,21/01/2021 17:55,"1 Sep, 2020 to 31 Dec, 2020",Matters involving public funds,Health,Access for Irish patients to a new treatment for atopic eczema,"Éamon Ó Cuív|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Neasa Hourigan|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Róisín Shorthall|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Colm Burke|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Alan Kelly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::David Cullinane|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Pa Daly|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas::Joe O'Brien|TD|Dáil Éireann, the Oireachtas",To secure access for Irish patients to a new treatment for atopic eczema,"An e-mail was sent to every supporter of the Irish Skin Foundation, with an interest in atopic eczema, requesting that they write to their local TD to seek their assistance in raising the matter of access to a new treatment for atopic eczema with the Minister for Health and the HSE.|Email|100+",David McMahon,No,,True,To consider writing to their local TDs to highlight the undue delay being experienced by Irish patients in securing access to a new treatment for atopic eczema,False,
