nad::Victor Boyhan|Senator|Seanad::Lynn Boylan|Senator|Seanad::Paddy Burke|Senator|Seanad::Malcolm Byrne|Senator|Seanad::Micheál Carrigy|Senator|Seanad::Pat Casey|Senator|Seanad::Shane Cassells|Senator|Seanad::Lorraine Clifford-Lee|Senator|Seanad::Martin Conway|Senator|Seanad::Gerard Craughwell|Senator|Seanad::Ollie Crowe|Senator|Seanad::John Cummins|Senator|Seanad::Emer Currie|Senator|Seanad","Congress wrote to all Ministers, Senators and TDS in relation to the EU Canada Trade Agreement urge Government to defer tabling any such motion until the Oireachtas has an opportunity to have a full exchange of views on this matter. We note that 11 other member states as well as Canada are still considering the ratification of this agreement so there is no need for Ireland to rush to ratify this agreement without proper scrutiny and debate.",|Email|1,"Patricia King, General Secretary ICTU",No,,False,,False,
